You can learn a lot from Dmitry Galkovsky's meals on air during his lectures. Cream cheese imported from Finland, fresh ham, mug of beer. Beer with canned sturgeon. Brown bread with goose liver pate and beer. Swedish crispbreads with extra salt and again a mug of beer. Genius.
Chesterton and the Englishmen in general have it right. You can never go wrong with a bread, ham, and cheese combination with beer. It's simply very hard to beat as a meal in terms of comfort.
